body:
Here's another (#219) issue with the explicit resizing. Consider the following `Main.sv`:

```
module Main();
   logic[4:0] r5;

   initial begin
      r5 = logic[4:0]'(3'd7 + 3'd6);
      $display("r5 = %b, %d", r5, r5);

      $finish();
   end

endmodule
```

Doing `iverilog -g2012 Main.sv && ./a.out` gives

```
r5 = 00101,  5
```

However, I think the correct result it 13. The SystemVerilog-2017 standard on p. 132 says:

> If the expression is assignment compatible with the casting type, then the cast shall return the value that a variable of the casting type would hold after being assigned the expression.

And this does not hold true in the above `Main` module:

```
module Main();
   logic[4:0] r5;
   logic [4:0] tmp;

   initial begin
      tmp = 3'd7 + 3'd6;
      r5 = tmp;
      
      $display("r5 = %b, %d", r5, r5); // gives r5 = 01101, 13

      $finish();
   end

endmodule
```

